    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - TROUBLESHOOTING VIBRATIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING VIBRATIONS</title>
        <para>Before troubleshooting a vibration condition, make sure of the following:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The engine idle speed is within the specified range.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The engine is operating correctly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The U-joints, yoke and driveshaft are in good condition. Check the driveline angles. Correct
                as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The U-joints, yokes and driveshafts are correctly aligned and/or balanced. Correct as
                necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check suspension air bag height. Correct as necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t1303306">
            <title>Troubleshooting Vibrations</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.46in"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.52in"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.47in"/>
                <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Condition</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Possible Cause</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Remedy</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>1. Vibration</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>1. Loose fasteners.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>1. Tighten fasteners. If fasteners do not remain tight, replace fasteners or
                                housing.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>2. Damaged bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>2. Replace bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>3. Broken or loose synchronizer pins.*</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col3">
                            <para>3. Replace synchronizer.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                            <para>*If the transmission does not shift correctly into the selected range, broken or loose
                                synchronizer pins are the result of the vibration condition.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
